  h2.slab.bg4 4/ Galvanize followers
  p The great thing about bringing people on the journey is they'll help you bring even more people.
  p For example, watch how Mark motivates his followers to get #LadBaby trending on Twitter. All perfectly timed for their song launch.
  video(src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/lad4.mp4" class="img__100" playsinline="playsinline" poster="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lad4.png" onclick="this.paused ? this.play() : this.pause();")
  h2.slab.bg5 5/ Know what turns the needle
  p Momentum or not, there's no way Mark and Rox can outstream Mariah Carey.
  p But they don’t have to. The way UK charts are calculated 1 paid download equals 100 streams.
  p So Mark and Rox’s focus exclusively on downloads. And they treat every vlog, radio, TV appearance as mini-adverts to download the track.
  p Based on streaming numbers they don’t make the charts. But the weighting of downloads makes them pretty much untouchable.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lad5.png" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__100
  h2.slab.bg1 5/ So there we go
  p How to run a marketing campaign:
  p.inwardSpeech Have a story. Make something viral. Bring people on the journey. Use momentum to create more momentum. And you'll create potential energy
  p But the one thing missing is soul.


